author: knoxnews.com
title: Football rankings for Week 8 - PrepXtra
text:
Top 10
1. (1) Maryville (7-0)
Last Week: Beat Dobyns-Bennett 49-10; This Week: Idle
Skinny: Rebels have won 37 consecutive games and 56 straight in regular season.
2. (2) Alcoa (6-1)
Last Week: Beat McMinn Central 38-7; This Week: Idle
Skinny: Tornadoes have outscored opponents 271-61 this season.
3. (3) Fulton (6-1)
Last Week: Beat Carter 71-14; This Week: Idle
Skinny: Falcons averaging 56.6 points during five-game winning streak.
4. (4) CAK (8-0)
This Week: Beat Clinton 42-21; Next Week: at McMinn Central
Skinny: Warriors off to fourth 8-0 start in past seven seasons.
5. (5) Morristown West (6-1)
Last Week: Beat Morristown East 35-0; This Week: Idle
Skinny: Trojans are 6-1 for first time since 2011.
6. (6) Farragut (6-0)
Last Week: Beat Campbell County 31-0; This Week: vs. West
Skinny: Admirals haven't started 7-0 since 2008.
7. (7) Oak Ridge (7-1)
This Week: Beat McMinn County 24-0; Next Week: Idle
Skinny: Wildcats wide receiver Tee Higgins, a Tennessee commit, caught a TD pass and had an interception on Thursday.
8. (8) Greeneville (5-1)
Last Week: Beat Grainger 35-0; This Week: at Sullivan South
Skinny: Greene Devils, 3-0 in Region 1-4A this season, have won 48 consecutive region games.
9. (9) Central (5-1)
Last Week: Beat Union County 58-0; This Week: vs. Halls
Skinny: Bobcats have won past five in series against non-region rival.
10. (10) Sevier County (4-2)
Last Week: Beat Daniel Boone 42-28; This Week: vs. David Crockett
Skinny: Smoky Bears one of three teams unbeaten in Region 1-5A.
Chris Thomas
